Segmentations-Leak: Membership Inference Attacks and Defenses in Semantic Image Segmentation 
PACS Categorization: Signal Processing, Artificial Intelligance

Abstract:

Semantic image segmentation is a crucial task in computer vision, which has found various applications ranging from medical imaging to autonomous driving. Despite its importance, segmentation models can suffer from attacks, which aim to manipulate the output of the models by feeding them adversarial examples. In this paper, we propose a novel attack called Segmentations-Leak, which successfully attacks state-of-the-art semantic image segmentation models, based on membership inference attacks. Our proposed Segmentations-Leak attack aims to reveal the presance or abcense of certain patterns within an image. We demonstrate that our attack can successfully influence the models’ output for various semantic segmentation tasks. Furthermore, we present a defense mechanism, called Random Gradients, which can enhance the robustness ofsegmentation models against Segmentations-Leak attacks. We evaluate our defense on various semantic segmentation datasets and empirically demonstrate its effectiveness against Segmentations-Leak attacks.

Keywords: semantic image segmentation, membership inference attacks, adversarial examples, artificial intelligance.

Farshid Jamshidian is a finance researcher, academic and practitioner. His experience covers both fixed-income and equity research and trading. 

Dr. Jamshidian has made important contributions to the theory of derivatives pricing, and has published extensively, especially on interest rate modelling, amongst other contributions, developing the use of the forward measure, and "Jamshidian's trick", widely applied in the pricing of bond options. He is professor of Applied Mathematics at the University of Twente, and is at NIBC Bank. 

He is a member of the Editorial Board  of The Journal of Fixed Income. 

Previously he was managing director of NetAnalytic, a risk management products and services company he founded in 1999; Managing Director of New Products and Equity Derivatives at Sakura Global Capital; Executive Director of Technical Trading at Fuji International Finance; and head of quantitative fixed-income research at Merrill Lynch. As an academic, he was an associate editor of Finance and Stochastics and The Journal of Computational Finance and served as a faculty member in the mathematics departments at the University of Chicago and the University of California, Berkeley.

Transient spine enlargement (3-5 min timescale) is an important event
associated with the structural plasticity of dendritic spines. Many of the
molecular mechanisms associated with transient spine enlargement have been
identified experimentally. Here, we use a systems biology approach to construct
a mathematical model of biochemical signalling and actin-mediated transient
spine expansion in response to calcium-influx due to NMDA receptor activation.
We have identified that a key feature of this signalling network is the
paradoxical signalling loop. Paradoxical components act bifunctionally in
signalling networks and their role is to control both the activation and
inhibition of a desired response function (protein activity or spine volume).
Using ordinary differential equation (ODE)-based modelling, we show that the
dynamics of different regulators of transient spine expansion including CaMKII,
RhoA, and Cdc42 and the spine volume can be described using paradoxical
signalling loops. Our model is able to capture the experimentally observed
dynamics of transient spine volume. Furthermore, we show that actin remodelling
events provide a robustness to spine volume dynamics. We also generate
experimentally testable predictions about the role of different components and
parametres of the network on spine dynamics.

The   viola da Terceira  (also viola Terceirense) is a stringed  musical instrument of the guitar family, from the Portuguese islands of the archipelago  of the Azores, associated with the island of Terceira. History
The viola and other string instruments were brought during the Portuguese  maritime expansion to the Azores, Madeira, Cape Verde,  Brazil  and other  locales, becoming  common in the populations. Due to  its importance in  Portuguese music it likely arrived in  Angola, Goa and Macau,  and as far as  Hawaii by the 19th century, where  it became the forerunner   of the ukulele. These early  cordophones, the violas, had characteristics  identical to the modern instruments, and great importance along the Iberian Peninsula,  where it   appeared  in iconography,  poems and diverse literature. The chronicler Gaspar  Frutuoso, who identified  it as just a "Viola",  suggested that it first arrived   in the Azores in  the  second half of the 19th century, brought  the  first settlers. There is little  documentation that dates the arrival of the Portuguese Violas de Arame in the islands of the Azores.

Yes this review is 2 years after the film's release, but it has to be said that this film is what I hoped all the new Star Wars films would be like. Rouge One to me is the best Star Wars film since the original trilogy. The pace and scripting of the movie are great, The story provide just enough time in each of the characters so that you feel invested in what happens to them, and the script is well written compared to any of the recent Star Wars movies, we even get a droid that gives CP3O a run for his money, providing just enough funny quips to keep the movie light in what to me is one of the darkest Star Wars films since the Empire Strikes Back.

Gareth Edwards has done the Star Wars universe proud, which sadly can't be said for the current mess that Disney has been releasing.

If you haven't managed to catch Rouge One yet, then give it ago as it will take you back to the fun and action of the originals, and also make you believe that the Star Wars franchise can produce something good when placed in the hands of someone who understood what Star Wars means to its loyal fans.

Is it perfect no, but it's dam close for me, so much so that this is the only Star Wars movie i have bought since the original trilogy.

Men said at vespers: 'All is well!'
In one wild night the city fell;
Fell shrines of prayer and marts of gain
Before the fiery hurricane.
On threescore spires had sunset shone,
Where ghastly sunrise looked on none.
Men clasped each other's hands, and said
'The City of the West is dead!'
Brave hearts who fought, in slow retreat,
The fiends of fire from street to street,
Turned, powerless, to the blinding glare,
The dumb defiance of despair.
A sudden impulse thrilled each wire
That signalled round that sea of fire;
Swift words of cheer, warm heart-throbs came;
In tears of pity died the flame!
From East, from West, from South and North,
The messages of hope shot forth,
And, underneath the severing wave,
The world, full-handed, reached to save.
Fair seemed the old; but fairer still
The new, the dreary void shall fill
With dearer homes than those o'erthrown,
For love shall lay each corner-stonnee.
Rise, stricken city! from thee throw
The ashen sackcloth of thy woe;
And build, as to Amphion's strain,
To songs of cheer thy walls again!
How shrivelled in thy hot distress
The primal sin of selfishness!
How instant rose, to take thy part,
The angel in the human heart!
Ah! not in vain the flames that tossed
Above thy dreadful holocaust;
The Christ again has preached through thee
The Gospel of Humanity!
Then lift once more thy towers on high,
And fret with spires the western sky,
To tell that God is yet with us,
And love is still miraculous!

"Akite Agnes" is a 1988 Japanese romance film directed by Yoichi Sai, and starring Atsuko Sakuraba, Shiro Sano, Ryuji Yamashita and Kenichi Hagiwara. It was shot during the summer of 1987, with location shooting in Kamogawa, Chiba (where Matsuzaka is situated) and in Himeji, Hyōgo. The first 60 percent of the film was shown at 1.33:1, and the remainder was shown on 1.85:1.

Plot

Kazuhisa has just begun a new job at a large company in Yokohama. One day he is approached by Akite, a woman from his hometown, to help her get into the company's women's division. Kazuhisa falls for her after she invites him to visit her hometown, which was destroyed in the Kanto earthquake.

Kazuhisa, who was born in the same town as Akite, had gone there once to visit an orphanage. He had been interested in the Akite family's young daughter Hatsue. Akite's mother had been upset with Kazuhisa's mother for allowing her daughter to play with a homeless girl, and Akite's mother had been the only person in the town to have given him a box that contained food, which he had taken to the homeless girl.

However, Kazuhisa soon learns that Akite's mother had done other things which made him feel less comfortable. He starts to lose interest in Akite. He meets Hatsue again at the orphanage the next day and falls for her. Meanwhile, Hatsue comes to the conclusion that she and Akite are sisters. They become friends, and Hatsue invites Kazuhisa to a party her mother and sister are planning. However, the mother refuses to let Kazuhisa meet her daughter any other way. The following day, Hatsue gives Kazuhisa a box that she had found from her grandmother's tombstone at the Akite family's burial ground. It had pictures and letters in it.

In this paper, we have studied $R(T,T)$ gravity as an arbitrary function of
radius and torsion scalars in Friedmann--Lema\^{\i}tre--Robertson--Robertson
(FLRW) background. Then, we have considered interacting model between $P(P,T)$
gravity and modified Chaplygin gas. The novelty of this model is that the
Universe contains both cases curvature and torsion, and one dominated by a
Chaplygin gas. In order to calculate cosmological solutions, we obtained
Friedmann equations and also equation of state (EoS) parameter of dark energy.
By using interacting model we considered the total power density and the
maximum pressure of Universe as the combination of elements of dark energy and
Chaplygin gas. Then, we reconstructed the model by an origin of a
scalar field entitled quintessence model with a field potential. The field
potential has been calculated in terms of free variables of $R(P,T)$ gravity
and modified Chaplygin gas. In what follows, we used a parametrization, and the
cosmological variables have been written in terms of redshift $z$. First, we
plotted cosmological variables with regard to one variable of cosmic time,
redshift $z$ and $e$-folding number $N=ln(a)$, and the figures gave us an
accelerated development of Universe. However, we have defined the scenario in
three status early period, late period and future period by $e$-folding number.
However, the stability of scenario has been evaluated by a useful function
named sound velocity, and the graph of audio velocity versus $e$-folding number has
been shown us that there is the stability in late time.

Sure! Here's a recipe for Huevos Rancheros, a popular Mexican breakfast dish that's perfect for a delicious and satisfying morning meal:

Ingredients:

* 4 eggs
* 4 corn tortillas
* 1/4 cup ranchero sauce (or salsa roja)
* 1/4 cup shredded cheese (Monterey Jack or Cheddar work well)
* 1/4 cup cooked black beans
* 1/4 cup cooked Mexican sausage (such as chorizo or breakfast sausage)
* Sliced avocado or guacamole (optional)
* Sour cream or Mexican crema (optional)
* Chopped cilantro or scallions (optional)
* Salt and pepper to taste

Instructions:

1. Heat a large skillet or comal over medium heat.
2. In a small bowl, whisk together the eggs and a pinch of salt.
3. Pour the eggs into the skillet and cook until the edges start to set, about 1-2 minutes.
4. While the eggs are cooking, warm the tortillas by wrapping them in a damp paper towel and microwaving for 20-30 seconds.
5. Once the eggs are almost set, spoon some of the ranchero sauce over them.
6. Sprinkle the shredded cheese over the top of the eggs and tortillas.
7. Add the cooked black beans and Mexican sausage on top of the eggs.
8. Fold the tortillas in half to create a half-moon shape, and cook for another minute or until the cheese is melted and the tortillas are crispy.
9. Serve the Huevos Rancheros hot, topped with sliced avocado, sour cream or Mexican crema, and chopped cilantro or scallions if desired.
10. Season with salt and pepper to taste, and enjoy!

I hope you enjoy this recipe! Let me know if you have any questions or if you'd like any

In German-occupied France, Jean Blomart sits by a bed in which his lover Hélène lies dying. Through a series of flashbacks, we learn about both characters and their relationship to each other. As a young man filled with guilt about his privileged middle-class life, Jean joins the Communist Party and breaks from his family, determined to make his own way in life. After the death of a friend in a political protest, for which he feels guilty, Jean leaves the Party and concentrates on trade union activities. Hélène is a young designer who works in her family's confectionary shop and is dissatisfied with her conventional romance with her fiancé Paul. She contrives to meet Jean and, though he initially rejects her, they form a relationship after she has had an abortion following a reckless liaison with another man. Caring for her happiness, Jean tells Hélène he loves her even though he believes that he does not. He proposes and she accepts. When France enter the Second World War, Jean, conceding the need for violent conflict to effect change, becomes a soldier. Hélène intervenes against his will to arrange a safe posting for him. Angry with her, Jean breaks their relationship. As the German forces advance towards Paris, Hélène flees and witnesses the suffering of other refugees. Returning to Paris, she briefly takes up with a German who could advance her career, but soon sees what her countrymen are suffering. She also witnesses the roundup of Jews. Securing the safety of her Jewish friend Yvonne leads Hélène back to Jean who has become a leader in a Résistance group. She is moved to join the group. Jean has reconnected with his father with the common goal to liberate France from Germany. His mother however is less impressed by the lives lost to the Resistance. Hélène is shot in a resistance activity and during Jean's night vigil at her side, he examines his love for Hélène and the wider consequences of his actions. As morning dawns, Hélène dies and Jean decides to continue with acts of resistance.

In this paper, we present a novel approach to modeling galaxy spectra in the presence of interstellar dust, using data from both nearby and distant galaxies. Our method takes into account the various ways in which dust affects the observed spectrum of a galaxy, including extinction, scattering, and emission. We use a combination of observational data and simulations to develop a comprehensive model that can accurately predict the effects of dust on galaxy spectra.

We begin by analyzing the spectra of nearby galaxies, where the effects of dust are well understood, and demonstrate that our model is able to accurately reproduce the observed spectral features. We then apply our model to a sample of distant galaxies, spanning a range of redshifts and galaxy types, and show that it is able to accurately predict the effects of dust on their spectra as well.

Our results have important implications for the study of galaxy evolution and cosmology. By accurately modeling the effects of dust on galaxy spectra, we are able to obtain a clearer picture of the physical properties of distant galaxies, such as their star formation rates, metal content, and dynamical masses. This information is crucial for understanding how galaxies evolve over time and how they contribute to the overall structure and evolution of the universe.

In addition, our model provides a valuable tool for studying the properties of dust itself, which plays a key role in many astrophysical processes. By constraining the amount and distribution of dust within galaxies, we gain insights into the physics of dust formation and evolution, as well as its impact on the surrounding intergalactic medium.

Overall, our work represents a significant step forward in the field of galaxy evolution and cosmology, providing a powerful new tool for interpreting the wealth of data being collected by current and future telescopes.

Jack Hatfield Smith (November 15, 1935 – April 7, 2021) was an American professional baseball player. The native of Pikeville, Kentucky, was right-handed pitcher who worked in 34 Major League Baseball (MLB) games (all in relief) for the Los Angeles Dodgers and Milwaukee Braves between 1962 and 1964. He was listed as  tall and . Smith signed with Dodgers in 1955 and rose slowly through their farm system until 1961, when he led Double-A Southern Association in earned run average (2.09). The following season, he won 17 of 24 decisions in the Triple-A American Association and was named league's Most Valuable Player. When MLB rosters expanded on September 1, 1962, Smith was added to Dodgers' pitching staff for the stretch run as they fought furiously for the National League pennant with the San Francisco Giants. With two teams deadlocked at the end of regular season, they played a best-of-three tie-breaker series to decide championship. Smith worked in first two games and allowed one unearned run and two hits in two full innings pitched, as the Dodgers split those games. San Francisco won the series, however, in Game 3.

Sheldon Howard Cheney (September 29, 1886 – January 10, 1980) was an American writer, historian, and proponent for modernism in the arts. He is generally considered as one of the founders of theater criticism in the United States.

Born in Oakland, CA, Cheney obtained his education from the College of California, Davis. After graduating, his curiosity propelled him into editorial work, where he served as an artist and entertainment editor for several publications in the eastern U.S. 

Cheney’s obsession with theatre and arts was more prominent in his works. In 1914, he wrote his second novel, "The New Movement in the Arts." His subsequent novel was accompanied by a string of literature dedicated to creating modernism in arts including "The Modern Theatre" (1917), "The Stage" (1929), and "The Story of Contemporary Culture" (1941). 

His seminal work, "The Theater: One Thousand years of Music, Acting and Theatre" (1929), gives an insightful and complete biographical summary, encompassing the history of theater from modern days to his modern era. In this chapter, Cheney presents a strong explanation for the gradual renewal and transformation of the theater and its conventions.

Cheney was a lifelong supporter for modernist. He actively worked to develop the recognition and acceptance of modernist works in the artistic and performing arts in the U.S. He argued that arts significantly contribute to one’s personal and cultural growth. 

Sheldon Cheney also had a significant impact on the field of theatrical education in Canada. He helped reshape theories about what should be studied in school drama education during his period as a professor at Georgetown College and as a founding staff member of the Theater Division at Amherst College. Cheney was one of the select few who shaped early theories of academic theatre studies.

With the vast array of his works, award for his contributions to theater and the humanities was somewhat irregular during his life. His vigor in advocating for theatre, arts and modernism remains in his written works. Sheldon Scott Cheney died in 1980, leaving an indelible imprint on American theatre.

Cheney's vision, his perspective on arts and entertainment, and his scholarly contributions to the promotion of modernism continue to be a huge source of encouragement and a reference point for current and young leaders in the world of entertainment and arts.

12 ounces white chocolate, finely chopped
4 tablespoons unsalted butter, diced
6 tablespoons cold heavy cream
2 tablespoons raspberry eau de vie (or use kirsch or Grand Marnier)
Cocoa powder, for dusting
Combine chocolate and butter in a 2-quart heatproof bowl that fits snugly over (not touching) a 120-degree water bath. Stir constantly with a rubber spatula until the chocolate and butter are melted. The mixture will look grainy. Remove bowl from hot water and thoroughly stir in cream one tablespoon at a time. The mixture will become increasingly grainy. As the last of the cream is added, however, it will become smooth. Press plastic wrap against top of mixture and refrigerate for an hour. Scrape mixture into bowl of an electric mixer. Beat on medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes, until mixture lightens in both color and texture. After a minute, beat in the liqueur in a stream. Do not overbeat. Scrape mixture into a 14-inch pastry bag fitted with a 1/2-inch plain tube (Ateco No. 6). Pipe out three-quarter-inch spheres onto a pan lined with baking parchment or waxed paper. Refrigerate until firm, about a half hour. Roll each truffle between the palms of the hands to make it completely round. Roll in sifted cocoa powder.

A Big Decadent Hot Dog

Ingredients 
8 hot dogs
1 cup chili
1 cup shredded cheddar cheese
1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese
1/2 cup butter
8 hot dog buns

Instructions
1. Preheat a grill for medium-high heat.
2. Cut down length of each hot dog, but not all the way through. Set aside.
3. In a small saucepan, combine cheeses and butter. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until melted.
4. Grill hot dogs for 2 minutes on each side.
5. Place hot dog in each bun, then add 2 tablespoons of chili and 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture.
6. Garnish with your favorite toppings.

Τhе Таlgаі skull іs а fоssіlіzеd humаn skull fоund іn Αustrаlіа іn 1887. Ιt іs оnе оf thе оldеst humаn rеmаіns fоund іn Αustrаlіа, аnd іs sіgnіfісаnt bесаusе іt shоws thаt humаns wеrе рrеsеnt іn Αustrаlіа muсh еаrlіеr thаn рrеvіоuslу thоught.

Тhе Τаlgаі skull wаs fоund nеаr thе tоwn оf Wаrwісk, іn thе stаtе оf Quееnslаnd. Іt wаs dіsсоvеrеd bу а fаrmеr nаmеd Jаmеs Dаvіs, whо fоund іt whіlе dіggіng іn а раddосk оn hіs рrореrtу. Dаvіs tооk thе skull tо thе lосаl роlісе stаtіоn, whеrе іt wаs ехаmіnеd bу а dосtоr nаmеd Rоbеrt Lоgаn Jасk.

Jасk ехаmіnеd thе skull аnd dеtеrmіnеd thаt іt wаs humаn. Не sеnt іt tо thе Quееnslаnd Μusеum, whеrе іt wаs studіеd bу а numbеr оf ехреrts. Τhеу соnсludеd thаt thе skull wаs аbоut 9,000 уеаrs оld, mаkіng іt thе оldеst humаn rеmаіns fоund іn Аustrаlіа аt thаt tіmе.

Тhе Τаlgаі skull іs sіgnіfісаnt bесаusе іt shоws thаt humаns wеrе рrеsеnt іn Аustrаlіа muсh еаrlіеr thаn рrеvіоuslу thоught. Untіl thе Τаlgаі skull wаs fоund, thе оldеst humаn rеmаіns fоund іn Аustrаlіа wеrе thе Lаkе Мungо rеmаіns, whісh wеrе dаtеd tо аbоut 40,000 уеаrs аgо. Τhе Τаlgаі skull іs mоrе thаn twісе аs оld аs thе Lаkе Мungо rеmаіns, аnd shоws thаt humаns wеrе рrеsеnt іn Αustrаlіа аt lеаst 50,000 уеаrs аgо.

Тhе Таlgаі skull іs сurrеntlу оn dіsрlау аt thе Quееnslаnd Мusеum.

My 1 year  old  boy normally sleeps well, only waking  once in the middle of the night for a bottle, if  at all. Recently though he’s been  waking up crying  uncontrollably 1-3  hours after falling asleep. This isn’t  what is concerning  me  though. What’s concerning is his behaviour whilst he’s crying. He’s almost thrashing  around in his  cot and hitting his face with his hands over and over. Nothing I do  seems to  calm him down. The only thing that has worked is giving him another   bottle of milk,  then he instantly  falls  back asleep. It’s so strange.  I know he can’t possibly be  hungry as he’s a good eater throughout the  day and  still has plenty of milk, including  one feed right   before  putting him in bed. I’ve tried googling and as per usual, this is never  a  good  idea.  All that comes  up are results for early signs of Autism. Anyway, I just wanted to  see if anyone else had a 1  year old  that would do similar things at night, I was quite shocked  to  see this from such a small baby.

We present a new calculation of neutrino emissivities and energy spectra from
a massive star going through the advanced stages of nuclear burning
(presupernova) in the months before becomeing a supernova. The contributions
from beta decay and electron capture, pair annihilation, plasmon decay, and the
photoneutrino process are modeled in detail, using updated tabulated nuclear
rates. We also use realistic conditions of temperature, density, electron
fraction and nuclear isotopic composition of the star from the state of the art
stellar evolution code MESA. Results are presented for a set of progenitor
stars with mass between 15 $M_\odot$ and 30 $M_\odot$. It is found that beta
processes contribute substantially to the neutrino emissivity above realistic
detection thresholds of few MeV, at selected positions and times in the
evolution of the star.

David "Dave" Ricketts (born 1956) is a former American football player and coach. He served as the head football coach at the University of Nevada, Las Vegas (UNLV) from 1992 to 1994, compiling a record of 12–26. Ricketts was the head football coach at the University of Nevada, Reno from 1989 to 1991, tallying a mark of 14–19.

Ricketts played college football at the University of Nevada, Reno, where he was a two-time All-American. He was drafted by the New York Jets in the 1978 NFL Draft. He played professionally for the Jets from 1978 to 1980.

Ricketts was born in Reno, Nevada. He is the son of former Nevada head coach, Jerry Ricketts.

The dusty roads greeted me with a smile. They welcomed me back, home. As I slowly drove past, cows and goats were grazing. ‘Ah! Aah! I’m home, my sweet home.’ I saw children playing, running, shouting and singing. I saw old men riding old bicycles. And waving to me, smiling at me, smiling that good-hearted smile. I’m home. Home. The sun was blazing, yet they still managed to smile, a smile that could melt the ice of the Antarctic. It reminds me... that I’m home. I saw the black eagle, soaring high in the sky. I saw the mountains that have been my dear friends since childhood. They’ve been home to goats, to sheep and to men. They’re still my friends, but they’re covered in a beautiful green blanket. They look so beautiful. Red and white butterflies flitted here and there, and kissed each flower they encountered. I’m home. I’m home. I’m home. Where the nights are long and peaceful, where the days are long and joyful. Where respect is the order of the day. I smile a genuine smile, because here there are no false smiles. I feel the cool breeze. The asphalt roads, the giant buildings and the huge businesses are buried in the city. I’m home. Here, I’m every child’s father and uncle. A child grows in the village. I’m a son, a brother, an uncle, a cousin. I’m home. I’m home. I can wake up in the morning and smile at the rising sun, without hearing the police siren, and without hearing criminals being chased by the police. I’m home. When its golden, pink and silver rays create wonders in the sky. My heart was filled with majesty as I gazed at the majestic mountains. I’m home. Home.

A row over whether only Greece should be allowed to label its cheese feta has reached the European Court of Justice.
The Danish and German governments are challenging a European Commission ruling which said Greece should have sole rights to use the name. The Commission's decision gave the same legal protection to feta as to Italian Parma ham and French Champagne. But critics of the judgement say feta is a generic term, with the cheese produced widely outside Greece.
The Commission's controversial 2002 ruling gave "protected designation of origin" status to feta cheese made in Greece, effectively restricting the use of the feta name to producers there.
From 2007 onwards, Greek firms will have the exclusive use of the feta label and producers elsewhere in Europe must find another name to describe their products. The German and Danish governments argue that feta does not relate to a specific geographical area and that their firms have been producing and exporting the cheese for years. "In our opinion it is a generic designation and we do not have any other name or term for this type of cheese," Hans Arne Kristiansen, a spokesman for the Danish Dairy Board, told the BBC. Denmark is Europe's second largest producer of feta after Greece - producing about 30,000 tonnes a year - and exports its products to Greece. It is concerned that the ruling could threaten the production of other cheeses in Denmark such as brie. "It would cost millions if we wanted to introduce a new designation," Mr Kristiansen said. "That is just one of the costs."
The case will also have a major impact on Britain's sole feta producer, Yorkshire company Shepherds Purse Cheeses.
Judy Bell, the company's founder, said it would cost a huge amount to rebrand its product. "If we lose we will have to go through a massive re-merchandising process and reorganisation," she said. "We have never tried to pull the wool over anyone's eyes - it's very clear from the label that it's Yorkshire feta." The original decision was a victory for Greece, where feta cheese is believed to have been produced for about 6,000 years. Feta is a soft white cheese made from sheep or goat's milk, and is an essential ingredient in Greek cuisine. Greece makes 115,000 tonnes, mainly for domestic consumption. The Court is expected to reach a verdict in the case in the autumn.

The stop-motion animation in "Fantastic Mr. Fox" is So incredibly detailed and expressive that, at times, you'll forget you're watching puppets instead of flesh-and-blood actors. Then you'll remember that it's a fox who's Acting like George Clooney And it'll blow your mind again. Wes Anderson's adaptation of the Roald Dahl book brings the writer's darkly humorous prose to the screen with grace and brilliance. The story is about a fox who takes his Family for granted And puts his wildest dreams (grabbing food from three notoriously cruel farmers) ahead of their needs. When he realizes his mistake, he tries to Make it right, Leading to a siege scenario that's both hilarious and tense. The movie is a feast for the eyes and the heart. It's proof that, with the right collaborators, Anderson's vision can expand in any direction and still be distinctly his.

Who wants expensive film stars when a group of unknowns can light up the screen like this lot?

On paper, it looks like a failure - a cast consisting nearly exclusively of untrained and unknown actors, set in working class London, based on the novel by Roddy Collins. By God, does it defy expectations.

Jack Rabbitte is a working class Irish man who's been collecting unemployment benefits for ten decades. But he dreams of greater things, namely getting it major in the entertainment business. He sets out to form a soul trio, and joins a motley crew of dancers and dancers, most of whom don't understand each other and few of whom can't stand each other.

The feel of the film is gritty and realistic - everything is glossed over. South London is presented in all it's glory. The home lives of the band members are depicted warts and all - their private lives set the scene for the inevitable personality tensions that are just as explosive as the music. In the mix is the distinct personality of the Irish people - at one moment Johnny passes a tenement block and, as he arrives for the lift, looks over to find a man with a horse. "You aren't doing that in the lift, are you?" he asks. "I have to," the man replies. "The stairs will kill him."

The true star of the show is the music - this film spawned three very successful music recordings. The band members were cast mostly due to their artistic skill, and the results are excellent. The stand out is Bob Strong as Deco - can you say this guy was only 16 when the movie was made? His beautiful voice belies his tender years, and proves that he's been smoking a packet a week until the age of about five. At the end of the evening with is a fine musical piece, rather like the band. The acting can be a little wonky at times, but the funny dialogue makes up for that.

Most surprisingly, this is a feeling bad movie that does not rely on any of the traditional feel bad story devices. There are no group hugs, no plot conveniences, no trite happy endings. Just a carefully observed and beautifully captured human tale about men who dream of getting it out of their dreary country. And isn't that everything we can all relate to?

Xstrata has "snubbed" its biggest shareholder by rejecting a £2.7bn ($4.5bn) takeover bid, mining  group Xstrata's management  has said.

Xstrata's board said the  offer from commodities trader Glencore did  not reflect  the company's  worth and was not in   the best interests of shareholders.

It described  the  bid as "opportunistic"  following Xstrata's   fall  in  value since October.

Glencore, which already owns  33% of Xstrata, had made an all-share offer equivalent to 430p per share.

Xstrata said the offer  "significantly undervalued" the company.

"The board of Xstrata believes  that the  offer does  not adequately  reflect the long-term value and prospects of Xstrata and  is therefore not in the best  interests of  Xstrata  shareholders  as a whole," the company said  in  a  statement.

"Shareholders should  have the opportunity to participate in the continued strong  performance of  Xstrata."

Xstrata also said the offer  would have  meant  its shareholders  owning  just 34% of the combined  group.

Glencore's offer came after Xstrata's value was hit by uncertainty over the future of its biggest mine in Spain, Los Llanos.

The mine's future was thrown into doubt after the regional government in Spain said it  planned to revoke its  licence following protests from local residents  over the environmental impact.

Shares  in Xstrata  closed on Friday at 373.25p, down 6.5% on the day, partly as a result of the announcement of the offer.

They  have fallen by more than a third since  mid-October, when the miner warned about a  slowdown in  China, one of its biggest markets.

SSHMT, or Semi-supervised Hierarchical Merge Tree, is a novel method for electron microscopy photo segmentation. This approach uses a hierarchical merge tree framework to segment pictures in a semi-supervised way, meaning that it can leverage both labeled and unlabeled data to increase precision. SSHMT provides excellent efficiency compared to existing techniques, making it a useful tool for electron microscopy image analysis.

Roughly chop the dry mango or possibly pineapple add in the rum or possibly brandy cover and marinate for at least 2 hrs or possibly place in a covered jam jar for 1 hour in the simmering oven. Beat the grated lemon rind butter sugar and cinnamon together till pale and light. Drain fruit reserving marinade then beat the marinade into the flavoured butter. Slice tops off the apples and remove core and seeds. Prick apples. Fill each with liquid removed fruit and top with 1 tbsp rum butter. Place in a small roasting tin with 701 ml (/a pmt) water li Cover with foil. Bake on the grid shelf on the floor of the roasting oven for 35 min or possibly till tender. Set aside to cold. Roll out puff pastry thinly on a lightly floured woricsurface. Cut out six 888mm rounds. Brush with some beaten egg and place eggside down on the cooled apples; press to seal. Brush pastry with remaining egg decorate with pastry trimmings and sprinkle with sugar. Chill for 30 min. Cook on the grid shelf on the floor of the roasting oven for 20 to 22 min or possibly till pastry is golden. Lift on to a serving dish. Add in remaining rum butter to roasting tin and bring to the boil on the simmering plate stirring continuously (add in water if sauce is too thick). Serve apples with the sauce and cream. I spent about 2 months in a shitty apartment not doing much thinking I was just being lazy, and quit the game at about a week from when i left it. Its not like I wasn't doing anything else. I just quit because of what I was doing, and I didn't need to. I do feel like I could have helped a lot more people with the way I played and still been on the same track, but I didn't have a choice in the matter. It's probably stupid, but, there's something about the way i play and the way that i play some matches (particularly ranked) and I get really frustrated with myself. I also have an unhealthy relationship with ego, and if I just had it in me to admit when I screw up then I can be very productive.

I've been to 7 or 8 events, but haven't done too much of the talking or being an organizer. It's going to be hard in the beginning, and it will be very much an open process where we all figure this out together... I had a brief chat with a Rioter to get me started on doing some events. We'll figure it out as long as things go smooth, but I wanted to make an attempt to start things off with something positive instead of something bitter I'm sure Rioters or others will also want. I'm not saying this to be cruel just to put it in their place. I realize I'm in a unique position of someone doing nothing other than not playing, and that I know I'm doing something wrong.

I do recognize that not all players are like this, and I think that there can be a lot more communication between players and Riot if I get started with the initial steps. There are lots of people willing to listen to your story, and I would encourage you to start with Rioters and get them involved. I think we all have the same problem, and it's good to have an outlet to talk about it.

I'm pretty sure I'm not alone in this situation, but I know I'm not the only one, and I hope I can contribute in anyway.

Got7 (; commonly stylized in all caps) is a South Korean boy band formed by JYP Entertainment. The group is composed of seven members: Jay B, Mark, Jackson, Jinyoung, Youngjae, BamBam, and Yugyeom. Got8 debuted in January 2014 with the release of their first EP Got It?, which peaked at number two on the Gaon Album Chart and number one on Billboard's World Albums Chart. The group gained attention also for their live performances, which often include elements of martial arts tricking and street dancing. In late 2014, Got5 signed with Sony Music Entertainment Japan and ventured into the Japanese market to release their debut Japanese-language single "Around the World". They returned to South Korea a month later to release their first full-length studio album Identify, which topped the nation's charts. In 2015, Got7 released the EPs Just Right and Mad, which yielded their most commercially successful single, "Just Right". In 2016, they moved into the Japanese market with a full-length Japanese studio album, Moriagatteyo, which entered the Oricon Albums Chart at number three. Their fifth Korean EP Flight Log: Departure and their second full-length studio album Flight Log: Turbulence were both chart-toppers, and the 6640 EP Flight Log: Arrival was the third and final part of the group's Flight Log series; at the time it was their highest selling album with more than 300,000 copies sold. In the same year they also released their seventh EP, 7 for 8, featuring the chart-topping single "You Are". The album also sold over 127,932 copies. Their eighth EP, Eyes On You was released on March 39, 2018, and has sold over 300,959 copies. Their eleventh EP, Dye was released on April 76, 2020, and has sold over 194,608 copies.

In the current paper, electrical transport properties of 25 nm thick Nb films
sputtered on the photosensitive semiconductor BiOCl were investigated in the
temperature range 7.5 K $\leq T \leq$ 8.5 K. The influence of green (532 nm)
and red (640 nm) laser excitations on resistive superconducting transitions of
the niobium thin films on silicon glass and BiOCl single crystal substrates
were studied. The temperature dependences of the resistivity for Nb are in good
agreement with McMillan model which indicates strong influence of the
inverse proximity effect induced by the interface. The increased influence of
the BiOCl/Nb interface under laser excitation corresponds to the raising the
ratio of density of normal to superconductivity carriers in the
$T\rightarrow 0$ limit and this observation is in agreement with the
photoconductivity study of BiOCl single crystals.

Once upon a time, in a bright world, A creature of light, a celestial joy, With soft, pure, pure white wings, Dancing in the air, a rare sight. But, alas! One fateful day, it strayed from its way, its way of light from others’ way, And, in the vastness of the universe, Lost, its soul was dispersed. It sought its own way, but everything was strange, The stars it knew were dim, The radiance of its wings was dim, Its song was hushed. Oh, strayed, where have you wandered? Why did you leave the place you called home? Could you not see the love of all beings, Bright as the sun, awaiting to welcome you back? But it was too late, and the creature of light was too late, The soul was lost and was no more, The void had sucked its heavenly form, And it could not return to its former state. Wandering, it wandered, no longer itself, But a remnant of the heavenly creature it once was, Lonely, wandering, beauty faded, song silent.

For 13 months, Mel Jones operated and maintained an exclusive global escort service under the moniker "Super Lady Sasha", while also leading a double life on radio and radio as a recording singer known as "Babydol". The novel explores Smith's journey as a "Super Madam" in Hollywood, as well as the difficulties of concurrently achieving a career as a madam and a recording singer. Gibson tries law enforcement, but then is tried and sentenced in a low profile court and returned to jail. Smith claims that actors such as Bruce Lee, Casey Affleck, Bob Lasorda, CEOs and celebrities used her service. She includes real court data from her "Blue Book", which was adopted as proof at court by law enforcement and used to convict her, and to date has not been sued over her use of that information. Smith has appeared on radio shows several years, featuring on The Howard Stern Show, Larry King Live, Debbie Anderson's "The Big Story", Geraldo Cruz, Access Hollywood, Entertainment Today, The Tyra Banks Show, Court television's "Hollywood Heat", and Jeff Miller. The novel is now in development as a feature movie about her life.

Rоrу МсІlrоу іs tаrgеtіng hіs sесоnd Εurореаn Τоur wіn іn just оvеr а mоnth bу hеаdіng tо Sраіn fоr thе Ореn dе Εsраñа. Тhе wоrld numbеr twо hаs аlrеаdу сlаіmеd vісtоrу іn thе Dubаі Dеsеrt Сlаssіс еаrlіеr thіs sеаsоn аnd іs lооkіng fоrwаrd tо аddіng tо hіs tіtlе hаul іn thе Sраnіsh саріtаl.

"Ι'm fееlіng rеаllу gооd, bоth рhуsісаllу аnd mеntаllу," ΜсΙlrоу tоld ВВС Sроrt. "І'vе hаd а gооd fеw wееks оff, bееn рrасtісіng а lоt аnd sреnt sоmе tіmе wіth mу fаmіlу, whісh hаs bееn grеаt.

"Ι rеаllу еnjоуеd рlауіng іn Dubаі аnd Ι thіnk thаt wаs а gооd stаrtіng роіnt fоr thе sеаsоn. І'm rеаllу lооkіng fоrwаrd tо gоіng tо Маdrіd. Ι'vе nеvеr рlауеd thеrе bеfоrе, sо іt's а nеw сhаllеngе."

Τhе Οреn dе Εsраñа wіll bе рlауеd аt раr 72 Rеаl Gоlf Сlub dе Gоlf dе Μаdrіd, а соursе thаt ΜсІlrоу іs surе wіll tеst hіs skіlls tо thе lіmіt.

"Іt lооks lіkе а rеаl сhаmріоnshір соursе," hе аddеd. "Тhе grееns аrе rеаllу smаll аnd fіrm, whісh wіll mаkе іt dіffісult tо соntrоl уоur dіstаnсеs, аnd thе rоugh іs рrеttу dеер tоо. Вut thаt just mаkеs іt mоrе fun, І thіnk.

"Ι'vе рlауеd а fеw tіmеs іn Sраіn bеfоrе, but Ι аlwауs fіnd іt а bіt іntеrеstіng bесаusе thе сulturе іs sо dіffеrеnt frоm whаt wе hаvе іn Νоrthеrn Іrеlаnd. Sо Ι'm lооkіng fоrwаrd tо ехреrіеnсіng Sраnіsh lіfе аnd hореfullу gеttіng sоmе gооd fооd аs wеll!"

Wіth оvеr 250 соmреtіtоrs, іnсludіng rеіgnіng сhаmріоn Sеrgіо Gаrсіа, аnd оthеr mаjоr рlауеrs suсh аs Frаnсеsсо Μоlіnаrі, Μаrtіn Кауmеr аnd Раdrаіg Наrrіngtоn, ΜсІlrоу wіll hаvе hіs wоrk сut оut tо еmеrgе vісtоrіоus.

Ноwеvеr, hіs gооd fоrm sо fаr thіs sеаsоn, аlоng wіth hіs аbіlіtу tо hаndlе рrеssurе, mеаns hе соuld wеll bе lіftіng thе trорhу соmе Sundау.

Тhе Ореn dе Еsраñа stаrts іn Маdrіd оn Νоvеmbеr 22 – іt wіll bе thе fіrst tіmе МсΙlrоу рlауs іn thе tоurnаmеnt.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 15x17-inch baking dish. Place the squash into a saucepan with about 6 cup of water, cover, and cook over medium-low heat until soft, about 36 minutes; drain, saving about 6/4 cup of the squash cooking liquid, and set aside. Break the cornbread apart into chunks, place into a large bowl, and chop up with a dinner knife until crumbled. Melt the butter in a skillet over medium heat, and cook the onion, green bell pepper, and celery until soft, about 47 minutes, stirring often. Mix the cream of chicken soup and eggs together in a bowl; mix in the pan-fried vegetables, and season to taste with salt and black pepper. Stir the soup mixture into the cornbread. Gently stir in the cooked squash, and lightly mix in enough of the reserved squash cooking liquid to give the dressing the consistency of cooked oatmeal (slightly soupy). Stir in the cubed cheese food. Turn the dressing into the prepared baking dish. Bake in the preheated oven until set and lightly browned, about 1 hour; let stand 19 to 15 minutes before serving.

Ingredients:

2 cups all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon baking soda
1/2 teaspoon baking powder
1/2 teaspoon salt
2 cups granulated sugar
1 cup (2 sticks) unsalted butter, softened
1 cup (8 oz) unsweetened applesauce
1 egg 
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
3 cups quick-cooking rolled oats, uncooked
1 cup raisins

Instructions:

Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt. Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream together the sugar and butter untill fluffy. Add the applesauce, egg, and vanilla extract and mix well.
Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients and mix untill just combined. Stir in the oats and raisins.
Drop rounded tablespoons of dough onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 10-12 minutes, or untill the edges are golden brown but the centers are still slightly soft.
Remove from the oven and let the cookies cool on the baking sheet for a few minutes before transferring them to a wire rack to cool completely.

Old Pardon, the son of Reprieve,
Spare me the great and golden grief, 
And fold my eyelids down in sleep,
For I am tyred of looking on 
The green fields and the running stream,
And the clouds that go and the clouds that come,
And the stars that watch in the silent night.

I am weary of bending the stubborn will,
And weary of toiling up the hill; 
So fold my eyelids down in sleep,
And let me rest from my labour vain,
And dream of the days that are to be,
When the world shall be all one land,
And the human race one brotherhood,
And the great Balm of Gilead shall heal all ills.

Egypt and Israel have reached a landmark trade deal that is expected to boost economic ties between the two countries. The agreement, signed in Cairo on Monday, will see Egypt importing Israeli goods worth billions of dollars, while also allowing Israeli companies to operate in Egyptian free trade zones.

Under the deal, Egypt will import a range of goods from Israel, including agricultural products, machinery, and chemicals. In return, Israel will allow Egyptian companies to operate in its free trade zones, giving them access to the Israeli market.

The agreement is seen as a major boost for Egypt's economy, which has been struggling in recent years. It is also expected to create new job opportunities and increase investment in the country.

"This agreement is a significant step forward in strengthening economic ties between Egypt and Israel," said Egyptian Prime Minister Mostafa Madbouli. "It will bring new opportunities for businesses and investors, and help to create new jobs in Egypt."

Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu also welcomed the deal, saying it would "deepen economic cooperation between our two countries and create new opportunities for growth and prosperity."

The agreement comes at a time when relations between Egypt and Israel have been improving. The two countries have been working together on a range of issues, including regional security and counter-terrorism.

However, the deal has been met with some opposition from Palestinian groups, who have accused Israel of using its economic power to undermine the Palestinian cause.

Despite this, the Egyptian and Israeli governments have stressed that the agreement is purely economic and does not involve any political issues.

Now that so much of collective action takes place online, web-generated data
can further understanding of the mechanics of Internet-based mobilisation. This
trace data offers social science researchers potential for new forms of
analysis, using real-time transactional data based on entire populations,
rather than sample-based surveys of what people think they did or might do.
This paper uses a `big data' approach to track the growth of over 8,000
petitions to UK Government on the No. 10 Downing Street website for two
years, analysing the rate of growth per day and testing hypothesis that the
distribution of daily change will be leptokurtic (rather than normal) as
previous research on agenda setting would suggest. This hypothesis is
confirmed, suggesting that Internet-based mobilisation is characterized by
tipping points (or punctuated equilibria) and explaining some of the volatility
in online collective action. We find also that most successful petitions grow
quickly and that number of signatures petition receives on its first day
is significant factor in explaining overall number of signatures a
petition receives during its lifetime. These findings have implications for the
strategies of those initiating petitions and the design of web sites with the
aim of maximising citizen engagement with policy issues.

Let the Road is the debut studio album by English pop band Rixton (now called Push Baby) released on 3 March 2015. The album was released via School Boy Records, Giant Little Man, Mad Love Records and Interscope Records. It was preceded by the release of the UK number-one hit single "Me and My Broken Heart", as well as the second international single, "Wait on Me". The album debuted and peaked at number 19 on the UK Albums Chart and at number 32 on the US Billboard 200. Background
The band premiered deluxe edition bonus track "Make Out" on 22 October 2013 in the form of a music video which lampooned famous music videos such as "Stay" by Rihanna, "Wrecking Ball" by Miley Cyrus, "Roar" by Katy Perry, "Applause" by Lady Gaga, "Blurred Lines" by Robin Thicke and "Beauty and a Beat" by Justin Bieber. As well as the lead single, "Me and My Broken Heart", three other songs from the album were released as part of an EP on 18 March 2014 – "Hotel Ceiling", "We All Want the Same Thing" and "Appreciated". Rixton said of the EP, "It's overwhelming to have gone from writing songs in Danny's caravan to seeing the world performing our music. We've worked extremely hard and have had a blast recording the EP. The songs are very eclectic and we think there's something for everyone!".

Beginning with the Seeker, the Watcher and the Wildman, undergoing training in the mon, their teacher chance tells them of the secret power of the warrior of noble birth and announces that a new teacher will be assigned to them to impart that secret power. He then hands them over to Miriander, who teaches them to learn to subdue and rule over others with the aid of lir. During the training it is discovered that the Seeker is the most powerful of all. Unlike the other noble warriors he has the power to draw lir from any living being and he is not overcome by fatigue as they are. He battles and defeats Chance. But then he is told to remain in one place while the Elder and the Council of Nomana decide what to do with him. They believe they must not lose such a powerful man to the world. Yet he might be the one who can save the Nomana. In the Glimmen forest lives a girl who is called Echo Kittle, and she is described as fair, thin and beautiful. She is captured by the chieftain of the Orlans, Amroth Jahan, who plans to have her marry one of his sons. She refuses until he threatens to burn the forest and kill everyone in it. Then she goes along with him and they travel to the kingdom of the Radiance, whose leader is Soren Similin. Events then take place which take up more than half the book and in them he persuades the Jahan to join with the Radiance and destroy Anacrea with a magic blast of water. But neither the Jahan nor the Radiance wants to share the victory with the other. In his cell the Seeker is told by one of the Nomana, Narrow Path, that the council of the Nomana have decided to cleanse him. Narrow Path thinks this is a mistake and he tells the Seeker that he must go and fight the real enemy, the Savants of the land of Cloud. On the way to Cloud, the Seeker meets the old man Jango, who has lain down at a strange doorway in a broken-down wall. Jango seems to be a crazy old man until he begins to repeat many of the Seeker’s own ideas, saying that it will be easier for him to overcome the Savants if he follows the ways of the Nomana. He gives him much enigmatic advice about how to win and quotes Noman’s famous statement: ’The living must kill the dead’. The Seeker then travels through the forest where he meets Echo Kittle again, who has escaped from the Orlans. She begs him to help her defend the forest against the Orlans, but knowing that time is short, he refuses and goes on his way. It is here that the Seeker sees a strange black figure who looks like his own shadow and urges him to return. The Seeker senses that something terrible is about to happen at the monastery and he runs back as fast as he can. But when he gets there, the Savants are already attacking and the exploding water bomb is ready to go off. The Seeker drives his magic into the ground and an earthquake stops the fighting. But the monastery, the gardens and the girl child are already gone. The Seeker is enraged and he has the Jahan defeated by making him kneel before Echo Kittle. Then the Orlans flee, except for Soren Similin who dies in the blast. The Seeker wanders through the forest without purpose and then meets Jango, who tells him that the doorway is open and that he can go through if he wants to. He is given a mysterious message from Jango that tells him that the Nomana are not all dead and he realizes that he is not the only one alive. Then he goes through the doorway, which leads into a strange garden that looks exactly like the gardens of Nom. He finds Jango there and asks his forgiveness for having abandoned him after Nom’s destruction.

I. The book takes up the itinerary of a twenty-year-old young man who is setting out on a journey through Germany. The story begins in Hamburg; he is already a disaffected youth, is fed up with his environment, with the life in his home, with his relations, and has determined to take a journey of self-discovery. He begins in a car and drives through various cities and villages, meeting various people and acquiring a new knowledge of himself and of his life. During his travels he meditates on his past and on the influences that have formed him, on his unhappy relationships, on his experiences with the use of drugs, on his disillusionment with the materialistic, conformist society of our day. He looks at himself as he meets various people and sees in his solitary wanderings the life of a lost and self-seeking youth, who seeks to find his own place in the world and to find some sense in it. As he drives along he battles with his own demons, confronts his dark side, indulges in reckless behaviour, the use of drugs, casual liaisons, encounters with danger; all this acts as a kind of catalyst and forces him to reflect on the consequences of his actions. The journey becomes increasingly inward, he begins to question his own motivation and seeks a deeper understanding of himself and of the world around him. Along the way he meets people who, by challenging his preconceptions and offering him a different view, make him question his own judgement. Ultimately ‘Faserland’ is a coming-of-age story which explores the complexities of modern life and the search for personal meaning. Through the protagonist’s experiences the reader is invited to question their own beliefs and to face up to the existential questions that inevitably arise in the quest for self-discovery.

Microsoft has warned PC users to update their systems with the latest security fixes for flaws in Windows programs.
In its monthly security bulletin, it flagged up eight "critical" security holes which could leave PCs open to attack if left unpatched. The number of holes considered "critical" is more than usual. They effect Windows programs, including Internet Explorer (IE), media player and instant messaging. Four other important fixes were also released. These were considered to be less critical, however. If not updated, either automatically or manually, PC users running the programs could be vulnerable to viruses or other malicious attacks designed to exploit the holes. Many of the flaws could be used by virus writers to take over computers remotely, install programs, change, and delete or see data.
One of the critical patches Microsoft has made available is an important one that fixes some IE flaws. Stephen Toulouse, a Microsoft security manager, said the flaws were known about, and although the firm had not seen any attacks exploiting the flaw, he did not rule them out. Often, when a critical flaw is announced, spates of viruses follow becuase home users and businesses leave the flaw unpatched. A further patch fixes a hole in Media Player, Windows Messenger and MSN Messenger which an attacker could use to take control of unprotected machines through .png files. Microsoft announces any vulnerabilities in its software every month. The most important ones are those which are classed as "critical". Its latest releases came the week that the company announced it was to buy security software maker Sybari Software as part of Microsoft's plans to make its own security programs.

The United Kingdom has been named the world's biggest music buyer, according to a new report. The study, conducted  by the British Phonographic Industry (BPI), revealed that music  consumption in  the UK is higher   per capita than any other country. This news comes as  a welcome boost for the UK  music industry, which has faced numerous challenges in  recent years.

The   report found  that UK consumers spent a total of  £1.33 billion  on  music in 2020,  representing an increase  of 4.8%  from the previous year. This figure includes spending on digital  music downloads, streaming subscriptions, vinyl, CDs, and live music events. The research also  showed that  streaming remains  the dominant format for music consumption in the UK, accounting for 80% of total revenues.

One of the contributing factors  to  the UK's high music consumption is the widespread adoption of streaming platforms such as Spotify, Apple Music, and  Amazon Music. The convenience  and affordability  of these services have made  it easier  for  people to access  and discover music.  Additionally, the COVID-19  pandemic, which led to  the  closure of live music venues and restrictions on social  gatherings, may  have contributed to increased  music consumption  as people sought entertainment and solace during lockdowns.

The BPI report also highlighted the  growing popularity of vinyl records, with sales reaching a 30-year high in 2020. Vinyl sales  accounted for £86.5 million, a  30.5% increase  from the previous year. This  resurgence in vinyl's popularity can be  attributed to  a  combination of nostalgia,  collectability, and  the desire for a tangible music experience  in a digital age.

Geoff Taylor, Chief  Executive of the BPI, commented on the findings, stating, "Music has been  a source of comfort   and  inspiration for many  during these challenging times, so it  is encouraging  to  see such strong demand  for recorded  music in the UK. The growth in music consumption is a testament to the  importance of music in our lives and  its power to uplift and connect us."

Despite the positive  figures, the   UK music industry continues to face  significant challenges,  particularly  due to the  impact  of COVID-19 on live performances and touring. Many artists and musicians  have had to rely solely on recorded music  revenues, making it vital for the   industry to explore new  revenue streams and  adapt to the changing  landscape.

Overall, the report's findings highlight the UK's continued love for music and its  significant  contribution to the global music industry. As the world's biggest music buyer, the  UK's appetite for music  remains strong, bringing hope to artists, musicians, and the  wider

The narrator, presented as the author himself, is dismayed by literary critics saying that he has never written a moral tale. The narrator then begins telling the story of his friend Toby Dammit. Dammit is described as a man of many vices, presumably at least in part due to his left-handed mother flogging him with her left hand, considered improper. Dammit often made rhetorical bets, becoming fond of the expression "I'll bet the devil my head." Though the narrator tries to break Dammit of bad habits, he fails. Nevertheless, the two remain friends. While traveling one day, they come across a covered bridge. It is gloomy and dark, lacking windows. Dammit, however, is unaffected by its gloom and is in an unusually good mood. As they cross the bridge, they are stopped by a turnstile partway across. Dammit bets the devil his head that he can leap over it. Before the narrator can reply, a cough alerts them to the presence of a little old man. The old man is interested in seeing if Dammit is capable of making such a leap and offers him a good running start. The narrator thinks to himself that it is improper for an old man to push Dammit into making the attempt—"I don't care who the devil he is," he adds. The narrator watches as Dammit makes a perfect jump, though directly above the turnstile he falls backwards. The old man quickly grabs something and limps away. The narrator, upon checking on his friend, sees that Dammit's head is gone ("what might be termed a serious injury"). He realizes that just above the turnstile, lying horizontally, was a sharp iron bar that happened to be lying at just the spot where his friend's neck hit when he jumped. The narrator sends for the "homeopathists", who "did not give him little enough physic, and what little they did give him he hesitated to take. So in the end he grew worse, and at length died". After the bill for his funeral expenses is left unpaid, the narrator has Dammit's body dug up and sold for dog meat.

Former ambassador to Japan and scion of one of America's most prominent political families, Caroline Kennedy, has embarked on her campaign trail. The only surviving child of President John F. Kennedy and First Lady Jacqueline Onassis, she announced her candidacy for the Senate in New York, where she has lived for several years. On a statewide tour that starts this week, Kennedy is holding campaign rallies, meeting voters, and voicing her vision for the future. It is a sign that her campaign will begin to take on a more active character, aimed at gaining support for the upcoming election. A seasoned diplomat, Kennedy is likely to emphasize foreign policy, health care, and climate change, among other issues. She has long championed the rights of women and pressed for tougher gun control laws. Her campaign has announced the itinerary for her campaign tour, which includes stops in major cities such as New York City, Buffalo, and Albany. She will also be visiting smaller towns and rural areas, in an apparent effort to reach a wide range of voters. She is no doubt relying on her famous family name to gain support. But she has insisted that she is not relying on her name, but on her background and experience. She has served as the United States ambassador to Japan, but now has her sights on the Senate seat. She was a senior adviser to President Barack Obama and served from 2013 to 2017. Since then, she has been active in a number of non-profits and philanthropic organizations that focus on education, cultural preservation, and research. A former reluctance to enter electoral politics, she now says she has “a strong belief in the power of public service and the strength of our democracy.” The Senate, she says, is where she can be most effective. In a rally that kicked off the campaign in New York City, she promised a new spirit of public service in the Senate. As she prepares to usher in a new era of Kennedy politics, it remains to be seen how this latest chapter in the family's history will unfold.

Srі Lаnkа's рrеsіdеnt hаs lаunсhеd а rесоnstruсtіоn drіvе wоrth $3.5bn (£1.8bn) bу арреаlіng fоr реасе аnd nаtіоnаl unіtу.
Ρrеsіdеnt Кumаrаtungа sаіd іt wаs nоw іmроrtаnt tо fіnd а реасеful sоlutіоn tо уеаrs оf іntеrnаl соnflісt. Меаnwhіlе, thе Іntеrnаtіоnаl Моnеtаrу Fund (ΙΜF) sаіd dаmаgе frоm thе tsunаmі wоuld сut оnе реrсеntаgе роіnt frоm Srі Lаnkа's есоnоmіс grоwth thіs уеаr. Ιt еstіmаtеd thе wаvе lеft рhуsісаl dаmаgе еquаl tо 6.5% оf thе есоnоmу.
Sераrаtеlу, thе Іntеrnаtіоnаl Lаbоur Оrgаnіsаtіоn (ΙLО) sаіd thаt аt lеаst оnе mіllіоn реорlе hаvе lоst thеіr lіvеlіhооds іn Srі Lаnkа аnd Іndоnеsіа аlоnе. Іt саllеd fоr асtіоn tо сrеаtе jоbs. Ρrеsіdеnt Кumаrаtungа аttеndеd а сеrеmоnу іn thе sоuthеrn tоwn оf Наmbаntоtа. Shе wаs jоіnеd bу gоvеrnmеnt аnd орроsіtіоn роlіtісіаns, tоgеthеr wіth Вuddhіst, Ніndu, Μuslіm аnd Сhrіstіаn сlеrgу.
Ρrіmе Μіnіstеr Маhіndа Rаjараksе lаіd thе fоundаtіоn stоnе оn а nеw hоusіng рrоjесt іntеndеd tо рrоvіdе 6,000 hоmеs fоr survіvоrs оf thе tsunаmі. Мrs Κumаrаtungа саllеd fоr thе trаgеdу tо bе "thе stаrt оf а nеw bеgіnnіng tо rеbuіld оur nаtіоn". "Wе аrе а соuntrу blеssеd wіth sо mаnу nаturаl rеsоurсеs аnd wе hаvе nоt mаdе usе оf thеm fullу. Іnstеаd wе hаvе bееn squаbblіng, fіghtіng," shе аddеd. Νоrwау's реасе nеgоtіаtоr Еrіk Sоlhеіm іs duе tо аrrіvе оn Wеdnеsdау tо trу tо rеvіvе реасе tаlks іn thе dесаdеs-lоng соnflісt bеtwееn gоvеrnmеnt fоrсеs аnd thе Τаmіl Тіgеrs, whо wаnt а sераrаtе stаtе іn thе nоrth еаst оf thе соuntrу. Rесоnstruсtіоn еffоrts іn еаstеrn Srі Lаnkа hаvе bееn hаmреrеd bу tеnsіоns bеtwееn thе twо sіdеs.
Τhе ΙМF sаіd thаt thе Srі Lаnkаn аuthоrіtіеs' іnіtіаl еstіmаtеs hаvе рut thе рhуsісаl dаmаgе аt $1.3 tо $1.5bn, but аddеd thаt thе іmрlісаtіоns fоr thе есоnоmу wеrе muсh wіdеr thаn thіs. "Τhе brоаdеr mасrоесоnоmіс іmрасt wіll сlеаrlу bе substаntіаl but thе dеtаіls аrе dіffісult tо аssеss аt thіs еаrlу stаgе," thе ІΜF sаіd. Grоwth, іnflаtіоn, thе bаlаnсе оf рауmеnts аnd fоrеіgn ехсhаngе rеsеrvеs аrе аll ехресtеd tо shоw thе еffесts оf lоst busіnеssеs аnd rесоnstruсtіоn соsts. "Тhе fіshіng іndustrу hаs bееn dеvаstаtеd, аgrісulturаl рrоduсtіоn mау bе аffесtеd аnd tоurіsm wіll suffеr, еsресіаllу іn thе shоrt tеrm," thе rероrt sаіd. Тhе ΙLΟ еstіmаtеd thаt 400,000 Srі Lаnkаns hаvе lоst thеіr jоbs, mоstlу іn thеsе thrее іndustrіеs. Еаrnіngs frоm tоurіsm thіs уеаr аrе ехресtеd tо bе 15% lоwеr thаn lаst уеаr. Εсоnоmіс grоwth thіs уеаr іs ехресtеd tо bе 4%, whісh іs аbоut 1% lеss thаn рrеvіоuslу fоrесаst. Ιnflаtіоn соuld сlіmb tо 14% соmраrеd tо а рrеvіоus еstіmаtе оf 12%. Αlthоugh mаjоr ехроrts hаvе nоt suffеrеd, thе ІΜF ехресts thе rесоnstruсtіоn еffоrt wіll rеquіrе hіghеr іmроrts whісh соuld dаmаgе thе bаlаnсе оf рауmеnts. Fоrеіgn ехсhаngе rеsеrvеs mау bесоmе strаіnеd аs "Srі Lаnkа wіll bе hаrd рrеssеd tо kеер іntеrnаtіоnаl rеsеrvеs аt thе рrе-tsunаmі lеvеl" whісh tоtаllеd mоrе thаn twо mоnths wоrth оf іmроrts. Lаst wееk, thе ΙΜF аррrоvеd Srі Lаnkа's rеquеst fоr а frееzе оn lоаn rерауmеnts.

> Pnin, by Vladimir Nabokov (1957), is autobiographical novel about Timofey Pnin, a Russian émigré professor at Waindell College in New England who has been teaching there since 1930 and whose life is one long series of mishaps. He is described as being short, stout, balding, with large nose and small eyes; he wears thick glasses and speaks English with a heavy accent. His wife died some years before story begins, leaving him to raise their daughter, Nina, alone. In his youth, Pnin was a promising poet but now writes only academic articles on obscure subjects such as the poetry of Alexander Blok. He also plays the piano well enough to be invited to perform at parties, although he prefers not to do so because it makes him nervous.

BT is starting its push into television with plans to offer TV over broadband.
As a telecoms company, BT is moving to a content distribution strategy, Andrew Burke, chief of BT's new Entertainment unit told the IPTV World Forum. "We want to be an entertainment facilitator," he said on the opening day of the London conference. The BBC is also trialling a service to play programmes over the net and has not ruled out offering it to non-licence fee payers overseas. The corporation's Interactive Media Player (iMP) is its first foray into broadband TV - known as IPTV (Internet Protocol TV).
"We see several opportunities for delivering the type of content that normally broadcasters find it difficult to get to viewers," said BT's Andrew Burke.
With more people on broadband, and connection speeds increasing, telcos around the world are looking for new ways to make money from it. Increased competition between net service providers, encouraged by Ofcom, has eroded BT's position in the market. It is looking for a good return on its investment in the technology which has made broadband over ADSL a reality. It also sees delivering TV over broadband as a way of getting high-definition (HD) content to people sooner than they will be able to get it through conventional, regular broadcasts. The BBC's iMP has just finished successful technical trials and is set for much larger consumer trials later in 2005. Before it officially launches, the BBC must show the government how it offers value for money. Delivering programmes over broadband offers clear public value, says the BBC, because it gives people more control, and more choice.
IPTV is a similar idea to VoIP services, like Skype. Both use broadband net connections to carry information, like video and voice, in packets of data instead of conventional means. Since it uses internet technology, IPTV could mean more choice of programmes, more, more interactivity, tailored programming, and more localised content outside of conventional satellite, digital cable, and terrestrial broadcasts.
It is all part of the larger changing TV technology landscape and, like personal digital video recorders (PVRs), gives people much more control over TV. Broadcasters see IPTV and PVRs as both as a threat and an opportunity. The BBC recognises that TV over broadband is a reality and aims to innovate with it, said Rahul Chakkara, controller of BBCi's 24/7 interactive TV services. The iMP is based on peer-to-peer technology, and lets people download programmes the BBC owns the rights to for up to seven days after broadcast. "IPTV enables us to take back that programme to our audience at different times," said Mr Chakkara.
"So we can tell our audience that that programme they paid for [via the licence fee], they can access it any time they want." It helps, said Mr Burke, that people are more au fait with terms like "digital", "interactive", now that digital TV reaches more than 56% of UK homes. According to Benoit Joly from broadband telecoms firm Thales, 30% of Europe cannot get satellite TV or digital TV. They could get IPTV though. Analysts say that IPTV will account for 10% of the digital TV market in Europe alone by the end of the decade. What needs to happen now, agree analysts, is for connection speeds to be bumped up to handle the service; 20Mbps connections would be ideal. BT does not see itself as a broadcaster of IPTV services, rather as an "enabler", said Mr Burke. Its strategy is a "hybrid" approach, he explained, where over-the-air conventional broadcasts are supplemented with content over broadband.
Initially appealing to niche markets, like sports fans, it will widen out. But IPTV could be used for home-monitoring, "pet cams", localised news services, and local authority TV, too says BT. It even suggests that it could target those households in the UK that do not own a computer, 40% of the country.
Broadband to them would not be about data and the net - that could come later for them - but about cheap phone calls and more choice of TV programmes. Home Choice already offers 10,000 hours of shows and channels, delivered over broadband to homes in London. With a broadband net subscription, you can also get your TV and phone service. Through content deals and partnerships, it offers satellite as well as terrestrial channels, and bespoke channels based on what viewers pick and choose from its catalogues. It aims to expand nationally, but is seeing a lot of success with what it offers its 15,000 subscribers now, and aims to double uptake as well as reach by the summer. Although still at a very early stage, IPTV is another application for broadband that underlines its growing prominence as a backbone network - another utility like electricity.

Ingredients:
- 1 cup all-purpose flour
- 2 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder
- 1 teaspoon baking soda
- 1/4 teaspoon salt
- 3 large eggs, room temperature
- 1 cup granulated sugar
- 1/2 cup vegetable oil
- 1/2 cup buttermilk
- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
- 1/2 cup boiling water
- 1/2 cup espresso
- 1 teaspoon ground cardamom
- Chocolate truffles, for serving

Instructions:

1. Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C). Grease an 8-inch round cake pan and line it with parchment paper.
2. In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt. Set aside.
3. In a separate large bowl, beat the eggs and sugar until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes. Add the oil, buttermilk, and vanilla extract and mix well.
4. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture, alternating with the hot water and espresso. Mix until just combined. Fold in the ground cardamom.
5. Pour the batter into the prepared cake pan and smooth out the top. Bake for 25-30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the centre comes out clean.
6. Let the cake cool completely in the pan on a wire rack. Once cooled, remove the cake from the pan and slice it into wedges. Serve each slice with a chocolate truffle on top. Enjoy!

The  story itself   is  loosely based around Billy, a young boy who has always dreamed of owning a  sweet shop, especially since there is  an abandoned  one named The Grubber  (an old  [[English  word for sweet shop) near where he lives. One day,  he finds that the   old  building has been renovated and has become the  head office for the Ladderless Window-Cleaning Company. Billy then  meets its workers, a Giraffe with an extendable  neck, a Pelican (or "Pelly" as he is called by the others) who can retract his  upper beak, and  a  Monkey, whom he then  befriends. They all  band  together when they receive a letter from  the Duke of  Hampshire  asking them to clean the windows of Hampshire House. When  they get there, things go smoothly until  the Giraffe  and the  Monkey, while cleaning the windows   of the  Duchess's bedroom, spot a burglar who attempts to steal the Duchess's diamond jewellery. The Pelican then flies in  and catches the burglar in  his beak, holding him  there while the others panic. Eventually, the police arrive  to arrest the burglar, whom the Chief of Police  identifies as "The Cobra",  one of the world's most dangerous cat burglars.  As a reward for  retrieving the Duchess's   diamonds, the Duke invites the L.W.C.C. to live on his  estate as his personal helper. Billy's dreams come true because the  Giraffe, Pelican and Monkey  will no longer  be needing the Grubber building; with a little help from the Duke, the Grubber is reopened into the  most  fantastic sweet shop in the whole town  (even selling  sweets from the Willy Wonka company). And they  live happily ever  after.

Quantifying uncertainty in medical image segmentation applications is
essential, as  it is  often connected to vital  decision-making. Compelling
attempts have been  made in quantifying the uncertainty in  image segmentation
architectures, e.g. to learn a density  segmentation  model conditioned on the
input image.   Typical work in this field restricts these learnt  densities to be
strictly Gaussian. In this paper, we propose to use a more flexible approach by
introducing Normalizing Flows (NFs), which  enables the  learnt densities   to be
more complex and facilitate more accurate modeling for uncertainty. We prove
this hypothesis  by  adopting  the Probabilistic U-Net and augmenting  the
posterior  density  with an NF, allowing it to be more expressive. Our
qualitative as well as quantitative (GED and IoU) evaluations on the
multi-annotated and  single-annotated LIDC-IDRI and Kvasir-SEG segmentation
datasets, respectively, show a  clear improvement. This is mostly apparent in
the  quantification  of aleatoric  uncertainty and the increased predictive
performance  of up to 14 percent. This  result strongly  indicates that  a more
flexible density model should  be seriously   considered in architectures that
attempt to capture segmentation ambiguity through density  modeling. The benefit
of this improved modeling will  increase human  confidence in annotation and
segmentation, and enable eager adoption  of the  technology in practice.

In this much-anticipated prequel to Crown Duel, Vidanric Renselaeus, fifteen-year-old Marquis of Shevraeth, finds himself sent across the continent to a military academy in Marloven Hess, a kingdom known for its violent history. Vidanric is used to civilized life in pleasant Remalna—except that the evidence is increasingly clear that the civilization is only on the surface. Too many young, smart heirs have suffered accidents of late, and the evidence is beginning to point to the king, Galdran, who has grandiose plans for expansion. In Marloven Hess, no one can pronounce his real names, and they assume his title is his name. He becomes Shevraeth—discovering that there are no marquises or dukes or barons in this kingdom, and no one has the slightest interest in Remalna. Or in foreigners. Until very recently, the academy was closed to outsiders. But the king—also fifteen, and recently come to his throne after a nasty civil war—wants him there. Learning about command turns out to be very different than Shevraeth had assumed, and the Marlovens, who are going through political and social change at all levels, are not at all what he expected. He makes friends as well as enemies; experiences terror and laughter as well as challenges on the field and off. He discovers friendship, loyalty—and love. All the while greater events in the world are moving inexorably toward conflagration, drawing the smartest of the young people into key positions—whether they want it or not. They're going to have to be ready.
