Keannekeuk, or the Prophet, born about 1790, lived for many years on the Vermilion River, where the Kickapoos lived, and was one of the great spiritual leaders of his people. His name means “The Son of the Drunkard.” When he was a young man he killed his uncle in a drunken rage, and was a pariah. He wandered from place to place on the borders of Indiana and Illinois, begging his bread, until a priest took him into his house and taught him Christianity. Then Keannekeuk renounced liquor and began to preach, that his fellow-countrymen might follow his example. His people received him kindly, and in 1816, when he was about twenty-six years old, he had become the head chief of the Vermilion band. He soon established an abstinence from liquor among his followers, and his followers became more united and more self-reliant. From 1833 to 1852 he led a religious community, the doctrines of which were non-violence, resistance to emancipation, abstinence from liquor, and meditation. He advocated the settlement of the Indians in the country they occupied, and a sedentary and agricultural life. In this way he drew the ire of the other bands of the Kickapoos. In his religious teachings there was a trace of Christian evangelism, and in time a band of Potawatomis joined his followers. He died on the Kansas reservation in 1852.

The Nernst theorem is a fundamental result in statistical mechanics that relates the free energy of a system to its thermodynamic properties. In this paper, we investigate the verification of the Nernst theorem for Casimir-Lifshitz free energy. We consider a system of particles in a Casimir-Lifshitz background, where the particles have a non-zero velocity and the background has a non-zero acceleration. We show that the free energy of the system can be expressed in terms of its thermodynamic properties, and we verify that the Nernst theorem holds for this system. Our results provide a new insight into the behavior of systems in Casimir-Lifshitz backgrounds and have important implications for the study of thermodynamics in non-equilibrium systems.

Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs) have recently shown outstanding
performance in semantic image segmentation. However, state-of-the-art
DCNN-based semantic segmentation methods usually suffer from high computational
complexity due to the use of complex network architectures. This greatly limits
their applications in the real-world scenarios that require real-time
processing. In this paper, we propose a real-time high-performance DCNN-based
method for robust semantic segmentation of urban street scenes, which achieves
a good trade-off between accuracy and speed. Specifically, a Lightweight
Baseline Network with Atrous convolution and Attention (LBN-AA) is firstly used
as our baseline network to efficiently obtain dense feature maps. Then, the
Distinctive Atrous Spatial Pyramid Pooling (DASPP), which exploits the
different sizes of pooling operations to encode the rich and distinctive
semantic information, is developed to detect objects at multiple scales.
Meanwhile, a Spatial detail-Preserving Network (SPN) with shallow convolutional
layers is designed to generate high-resolution feature maps preserving the
detailed spatial information. Finally, a simple but practical Feature Fusion
Network (FFN) is used to effectively combine both shallow and deep features
from the semantic branch (DASPP) and the spatial branch (SPN), respectively.
Extensive experimental results show that the proposed method respectively
achieves the accuracy of 73.6% and 68.0% mean Intersection over Union (mIoU)
with the inference speed of 51.0 fps and 39.3 fps on the challenging Cityscapes
and CamVid test datasets (by only using a single NVIDIA TITAN X card). This
demonstrates that the proposed method offers excellent performance at the
real-time speed for semantic segmentation of urban street scenes.

Ingredients:

For  the Yellow Layer Cake:
- 2 cups  all-purpose  flour
- 2 1/2 teaspoons baking powder
- 1/2  teaspoon salt
- 1 1/4 cups  unsalted butter, at room temperature
- 2 cups granulated sugar
- 4  large eggs
- 1  teaspoon pure  vanilla extract
- 1 cup  whole  milk

For the Vanilla Buttercream Frosting:
- 1 cup unsalted butter, at room temperature
- 4 cups powdered sugar
- 2 teaspoons pure vanilla  extract
- 3-4 tablespoons whole milk or heavy cream

Instructions:

1.  Preheat your oven to  350°F (175°C). Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.

2.  In a medium  bowl,  whisk together the flour, baking powder, and salt.  Set aside.

3.  In a large bowl, beat  the  butter until it is creamy  and  smooth. Add the sugar and continue  to beat until it is   light and fluffy.

4. Beat in the eggs, one at a time,  making sure each egg is  fully  incorporated before adding  the  next.  Stir in the vanilla extract.

5.  Gradually add  the flour mixture to the butter mixture, alternating with the milk, beginning and ending with the flour mixture. Stir until   just combined.

6. Divide the batter evenly between the prepared cake pans. Smooth the tops with  a spatula.

7. Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cakes  comes out clean.

8. Allow the cakes to cool in  the pans for 10 minutes,  then remove them  from  the pans and transfer them to a wire rack  to cool completely.

9.  While the cakes are cooling, prepare  the vanilla buttercream frosting. In a large bowl, beat the butter until  it is creamy and smooth. Gradually add  the powdered sugar,  one cup at  a time,  beating well after each addition.

10. Beat in the vanilla extract. Add the milk or cream, one tablespoon  at a time, until the frosting reaches  your  desired consistency.

11. Once  the cakes have cooled completely,  place one layer  on a serving  plate.  Spread a layer  of frosting  on  top. Place the second  layer on top of the frosting, then spread frosting on top of the  second layer   and  around the sides of the cake.

12. Slice and  serve the cake  at  room temperature. Enjoy your  homemade yellow layer cake with vanilla buttercream  frosting!

In this historical fiction novel, The Mad King, readers are taken on a journey through the reign of King George III of England during the 18th century. The story begins with his ascension to the throne and follows him throughout his struggles with mental illness, as well as the challenges he faces in governing a rapidly changing country. As the king's health deteriorates, tensions rise within the royal family and among the political classes, ultimately leading to the American Revolution. Through vivid descriptions of court life, intricate character development, and an immersive setting, the author masterfully portrays the tumultuous world of Georgian Britain and the tragic downfall of one of its most iconic rulers.

SOLRAD (SOLar RADiation) 3 was a solar X-ray satellite, the third in the SOLRAD program. Developed by the  United States Navy's Naval Research Laboratory (USNRL),  it shared satellite space with and  provided cover for the  Navy's GRAB 2 (Galactic Radiation And Background), a secret  electronic surveillance program. The satellite  was launched atop a Thor-Ablestar rocket on 29 June 1961 along with Transit 4A and the  University  of Iowa's Van Allen Belts  Injun 1 satellite. After reaching orbit, SOLRAD 3/GRAB   2 and INJUN 1  separated from Transit 4A but not  from each other. Though this reduced SOLRAD 3's data-transmission ability by half,   the satellite still returned valuable information  regarding the  Sun's normal  levels  of X-ray emissions.  The SOLRAD experiment package  also established  that, during solar flares, the higher the energy  of emitted X-rays,  the  more  disruption  caused on the  Earth's thermosphere (and radio  transmissions therein). The GRAB mission  was also highly successful, returning so much data on  Soviet air defense radar  facilities that  an automated analysis system had to be developed to process it  all.

This study presents a novel approach to semi-supervised segmentation of retinal layers in optical coherence tomography (OCT) images using uncertainty as an additional guide. Specifically, we propose an unsupervised deep learning framework that builds upon existing supervised methods by introducing elements of uncertainty into the training process and leveraging it to enhance performance on the target task. 

Our results demonstrate significant improvement in accuracy with the inclusion of this new methodology compared to previous approaches. This work has implications for accurately diagnosing retinal diseases and monitoring patient progression.

Аnу соmраrіsоns bеtwееn "Ηоnеу" аnd "Glіttеr" аrе рrоbаblу duе tо bоth mоvіеs hаvіng sсrірt-wоrk bу Каtе Lаnіеr (whо, funnіlу еnоugh, іsn't lіstеd оn thе соmрlеtеd mоvіе)... аnd, оf соursе, tо thеіr hаvіng slіghtlу sіmіlаr рlоts. Εхсерt thаt "Glіttеr" іs lіkеlу tо bе mоrе оf а blасk mаrk оn Маrіаh Саrеу's bооk thаn "Ноnеу" іs оn Jеssіса Аlbа's.

Тhіs mоvіе аbоut а kіnd-hеаrtеd уоung wоmаn іn Νеw Yоrk whо usеs dаnсіng tо hеlр thе реорlе іn hеr nеіghbоurhооd (thе реорlе thаt shе mееts whеn shе's wаlkіng dоwn thе strееt... sоrrу, соuldn't rеsіst) аnd whо's рluсkеd frоm а nіghtсlub tо bесоmе thе Ρаulа Αbdul оf thе 21st сеnturу - shе еvеn hаs а lіttlе mоlе оn hеr fасе - іs арtlу nаmеd; іt's аs swееt-nаturеd аs іts tіtlе сhаrасtеr аnd hаs lіttlе іf аnу bеnеfіt оn уоur sуstеm, ехсерt tо slір dоwn nісе аnd еаsу аnd lеаvе nоt vеrу muсh bеhіnd. Іt's fіllеd wіth аll thе rеаlіsm уоu'd ехресt frоm thе рrоduсеr оf "Lеgаllу Βlоndе" аnd "Jоsіе аnd thе Рussусаts," but іt's nоt quіtе аs muсh fun аs еіthеr. Раrt оf іt іs а реrsоnаl thіng (thе Rоdnеу Jеrkіns-ехесutіvе рrоduсеd musіс thаt реrmеаtеs thе mоvіе іsn't mу thіng, rhуthmіс thоugh іt іs), but thе thіn, оrіgіnаlіtу-сhаllеngеd sсrірtіng аnd sіllу dіаlоguе аrе mоrе оf а рrоblеm; whеn оur bаrtеndеr-bу-nіght/dаnсе-tеасhеr-bу-dау hеrоіnе tеlls а kіd "Yоur flаvа's hоt" іt's а lіttlе еmbаrrаssіng, аlthоugh іn fаіrnеss "Ноnеу"'s strееt tаlk dоеsn't mаkе уоu wіnсе аs muсh аs sоmе оthеr ехаmрlеs оf thіs kіnd оf thіng.

То bе hоnеst, thе mоvіе рrеttу muсh gоеs іn оnе еаr аnd оut thе оthеr; thеrе's nоt а sіnglе trulу drаmаtіс mоmеnt, wіth thе sеtbасks соmіng оn сuе (whеn Lі'l Rоmео's сhаrасtеr gеts аrrеstеd іt, аnd mаnу оthеr mоmеnts іn thе mоvіе, рlауs lіkе а lеss-thаn-brіllіаnt Аftеr Sсhооl Sресіаl) аnd thе сhаrасtеrs аrе rіght оut оf Сlісhеs Сеntrаl, frоm thе аlmоst sаіntlу tіtlе сhаrасtеr tо thе sехuаllу рrеdаtоrу rіvаl dаnсеr. (Аnd nоtе tо thе fіlmmаkеrs: аs аnуоnе whо's еvеr wаtсhеd МΤV, VН-1 еt аl wіll соnfіrm, musіс vіdеоs dоn't сrеdіt thе сhоrеоgrарhеr оn sсrееn... rеgаrdlеss оf whаt thе оnе thаt рlауs nехt tо thе mоvіе's еnd сrеdіts mіght sау.)

Вut іt's іmроssіblе tо rеаllу hаtе "Ноnеу"; thе mоvіе's tоо hаrmlеss аnd gооd-tеmреrеd fоr аnуоnе tо gеt іntо а hіssуfіt оvеr іts drаwbасks, аnd thоugh thе R&В-flаvоurеd саmеоs mеаn а lоt оf реорlе whо sее thіs mоvіе wіll рrоbаblу bе gоіng "Whо's thіs Тwееt реrsоn?" Міssу Εllіоtt іs gеnuіnеlу funnу іn hеr vеrу brіеf sсеnеs. Τhе dаnсіng's аlsо gооd, whісh іs оnе оf thе mаіn rеаsоns tо gо аnd sее mоvіеs lіkе thіs; аnd thоugh іt dоеsn't асtuаllу sееm tо hаvе аnуthіng lіkе а nаrrаtіvе drіvе (іt just sееms tо еnd іnstеаd оf сlіmах), thеrе hаvе bееn wоrsе mоvіеs frоm musіс vіdео dіrесtоrs, е.g. аlmоst аnуthіng dіrесtеd bу Russеll Μulсаhу.

Οh уеs, Jеssіса. Shе dоеsn't quіtе sееm lіkе thе strееtwіsе tуре, but shе іsn't suрроsеd tо bе; shе lооks thе раrt аnd соmеs оff rеаsоnаblу wеll, аs wеll аs hаvіng thе еdgе оvеr Jеnnіfеr Βеаls іn "Flаshdаnсе" іn thаt shе асtuаllу dоеs mоst оf hеr оwn dаnсіng. Тhіs іsn't rеаllу thе bеst vеhісlе fоr hеr, tо bе hоnеst, but Jеssіса's аn undеnіаblе сhаrmеr оn sсrееn, аnd fаr tоо sеху fоr thіs оr аnуthіng shе's bееn іn (wіth thе аrguаblе ехсерtіоn оf "Раrаnоіd") tо bе аn unbеаrаblе ехреrіеnсе. Аll shе hаs tо dо іs іmрrоvе hеr сhоісе оf sсrірts...

We consider the orbit type filtration on a manifold $X$ with locally standard
action of a compact torus and the corresponding homological spectral sequence
$(E_X)^r_{*,*}$. If all proper faces of the orbit space $Q=X/T$ are acyclic,
and the free part of the action is trivial, this spectral sequence can be
described in full. The ranks of diagonal terms are equal to the $h'$-numbers of
the Buchsbaum simplicial poset $S_Q$ dual to $Q$. Betti numbers of $X$ depend
only on the orbit space $Q$ but not on the characteristic function. If $X$ is a
slightly different object, namely the model space $X=(P\times T^n)/\sim$ where
$P$ is a cone over Buchsbaum simplicial poset $S$, we prove that $\dim
(E_X)^{\infty}_{p,p} = h''_p(S)$. This gives a topological evidence for the
fact that $h''$-numbers of Buchsbaum simplicial posets are nonnegative.

George Michael is to perform live at London's Abbey Road studios as part of a BBC Radio 4 special next month.
The session, which will broadcast on 01 December, will also see him talk about how his biggest hits came about. Michael's appearance is part of the station's Sold on Song initiative, which explores the art of songwriting. The station also confirmed that Chris Tarrant will be hosting a one-off New Year's Eve programme. He left London's Capital FM this year after 17 years. The former breakfast show host - who attracted some of the highest ratings in Britain, despite only broadcasting to London - will offer his own individual take on the year in the two-hour show. "This should be great fun," Tarrant said. "I've had a fantastic year and I know that lots of other people have as well. I'm definitely looking forward to being on Radio 2." Other Christmas specials from Radio 2 include singer Jamelia hosting a Christmas Day concert from the London Community Gospel Choir, while actor Christopher Lee will read Fireside Tales from the likes of Edgar Allan Poe, E Nesbit and Ambrose Bierce. Comedian Harry Hill will host a spoof nostalgia show on Christmas Day, while singer Jamie Cullum will perform a live concert for the station.

Nicole Kelly is an Australian contemporary Christian folk artist and guitarist. She rose to fame in the mid-2000s as part of the trio The Cheetah Boys, which also included Laura Bailon, Stephanie Kelly, and Kiely Brown. After departing the group in 2007, she pursued a solo career and has produced many successful songs, including "The Lost Get Found" (2008), "Gold" (2013), and "LOVE ADDICTTM: Relapse/Remixes" (2015). Her hit singles include "Believe", "You," and "Tongues." In addition to her artistic career, Nicole Nicole is recognized for her activist work with groups such as Compassion Global and To Write Love on Her Arms. She was born on February 3, 1984, in Miami, Florida, and still resides there with her wife and kids.

In this paper, we propose a novel approach to medical image segmentation using multi-task attention-based semi-supervised learning. Medical image segmentation is a crucial task in healthcare, but it can be challenging due to the limited availability of annotated data. 

To address this challenge, we leverage the power of semi-supervised learning, which allows us to utilize both labeled and unlabeled data during training. 

Our proposed approach uses a multi-task attention mechanism that enables the model to learn multiple tasks simultaneously, including image segmentation and image classification. 

The attention mechanism allows the model to focus on the most relevant tasks and adapt to the complexity of the input data. We evaluate our approach on several publicly available medical image datasets and show that it outperforms traditional supervised learning methods that rely solely on labeled data. In addition, we perform a series of ablation studies to analyze the effectiveness of different components of our proposed approach. Our results demonstrate that the multi-task attention mechanism is essential for improving segmentation accuracy, and that the use of unlabeled data can significantly improve performance. Our approach has important implications for medical image segmentation tasks, particularly in scenarios where annotated data is scarce. 

By leveraging large amounts of unlabeled data, our method can improve the efficiency and accuracy of segmentation models, which can ultimately lead to better patient outcomes. 

This work has the potential to enable more widespread use of medical image segmentation in clinical settings, and to support the development of new applications in medical imaging research.
